<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="171" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,727,1222]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">
The long-standing concept of three species of 
<taxonomicName box="[688,840,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[688,840,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Melanostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Europe has been challenged by 
<bibRefCitation author="Haarto, A. &amp; Stahls, G." pageId="20" pageNumber="171" pagination="93 - 134" refId="ref19752" refString="Haarto, A. &amp; Stahls, G. (2014) When mtDNA COI is misleading: congruent signal of ITS 2 molecular marker and morphology for North European Melanostoma Schiner, 1860 (Diptera, Syrphidae). ZooKeys, 431, 93 - 134. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 431.7207" type="journal article" year="2014">Haarto &amp; Ståhls (2014)</bibRefCitation>
who used an integrated approach (morphology of adults in combination with ITS2 sequences) to revise the North-European species. The morphologically highly variable 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[862,1005,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mellinum">
<emphasis box="[862,1005,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">M. mellinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
turned out to contain two species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mellinum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">M. mellinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Meigen, 1822)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[310,646,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mellarium">
<emphasis box="[310,462,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">M. mellarium</emphasis>
(Meigen, 1822)
</taxonomicName>
. We identify our material from Central Europe using the key in 
<bibRefCitation author="Haarto, A. &amp; Stahls, G." pageId="20" pageNumber="171" pagination="93 - 134" refId="ref19752" refString="Haarto, A. &amp; Stahls, G. (2014) When mtDNA COI is misleading: congruent signal of ITS 2 molecular marker and morphology for North European Melanostoma Schiner, 1860 (Diptera, Syrphidae). ZooKeys, 431, 93 - 134. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 431.7207" type="journal article" year="2014">Haarto &amp; Ståhls (2014)</bibRefCitation>
as well as the keys in 
<bibRefCitation author="Speight, M. C. D. &amp; Sarthou, J. - P." box="[575,863,871,897]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" refId="ref22367" refString="Speight, M. C. D. &amp; Sarthou, J. - P. (2017) StN keys for the identification of the European species of various genera of Syrphidae 2017. Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae (Diptera). Vol. 99. Syrph the Net publications, Dublin, 139 pp." type="book" year="2017">Speight &amp; Sarthou (2017)</bibRefCitation>
and in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bot, S. &amp; van de Meutter, F." box="[944,1271,871,898]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" refId="ref18688" refString="Bot, S. &amp; van de Meutter, F. (2019) Veldgids Zweefvliegen. KNNV Uitgeverij, Zeist, 388 pp." type="book" year="2019">Bot &amp; van de Meutter (2019)</bibRefCitation>
. In accordance with 
<bibRefCitation author="Speight, M. C. D. &amp; Sarthou, J. - P." box="[208,498,907,933]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" refId="ref22367" refString="Speight, M. C. D. &amp; Sarthou, J. - P. (2017) StN keys for the identification of the European species of various genera of Syrphidae 2017. Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae (Diptera). Vol. 99. Syrph the Net publications, Dublin, 139 pp." type="book" year="2017">Speight &amp; Sarthou (2017)</bibRefCitation>
we found specimens which completely fit the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[1162,1314,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mellarium">
<emphasis box="[1162,1314,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">M. mellarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the range of morphological variation within the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[702,845,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mellinum">
<emphasis box="[702,845,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">M. mellinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex in Central European populations is apparently much wider than in the material studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Haarto, A. &amp; Stahls, G." box="[700,964,979,1006]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" pagination="93 - 134" refId="ref19752" refString="Haarto, A. &amp; Stahls, G. (2014) When mtDNA COI is misleading: congruent signal of ITS 2 molecular marker and morphology for North European Melanostoma Schiner, 1860 (Diptera, Syrphidae). ZooKeys, 431, 93 - 134. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 431.7207" type="journal article" year="2014">Haarto &amp; Ståhls (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, as a large part of our material does not fit unambiguously to any of these taxa. In particular, populations from the Alps and adjacent regions display confusing variation indicating that additional species could be involved. A detailed investigation of multiple characters including DNA markers are required to disentangle the complicated taxonomy of central European 
<taxonomicName box="[1277,1429,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1277,1429,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Melanostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. At present, we regard the species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[603,745,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mellinum">
<emphasis box="[603,745,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">M. mellinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex as unidentifiable, at least as far as populations from the Central European Alps are concerned. Consequently, we refrain from listing taxa other than those known prior to 
<bibRefCitation author="Haarto, A. &amp; Stahls, G." box="[180,445,1195,1222]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" pagination="93 - 134" refId="ref19752" refString="Haarto, A. &amp; Stahls, G. (2014) When mtDNA COI is misleading: congruent signal of ITS 2 molecular marker and morphology for North European Melanostoma Schiner, 1860 (Diptera, Syrphidae). ZooKeys, 431, 93 - 134. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 431.7207" type="journal article" year="2014">Haarto &amp; Ståhls (2014)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
